title: 9m111_fagot
body:
The 9M111 Fagot (Russian: –§–∞–≥–æ—Ç; "bassoon"; NATO reporting name AT-4 Spigot) is a second-generation tube-launched semi-automatic command to line of sight (SACLOS) wire-guided [[anti-tank missile]] of the [[Soviet Union]] for use from ground or vehicle mounts. The 9K111 Fagot missile system  was developed by the Tula KBP Design Bureau for Instrument Building. 

The missile is stored and carried in a container/launch tube. It is fired from a 9P135 launcher post, a simple [[tripod]]. A 9S451 guidance box is fitted to the tripod with the missile sitting just above. The 9Sh119 sight is fitted to the left side (from the gunner's point of view). The complete launcher system weighs 22.5 kg (50 lb). The gunner lies prone while firing. 

North Korea was said to have acquired a number of the systems during the late 1980s until the 2000s. These were subsequently reverse-engineered under the designation Bulsae-2. It was advertised under designation AT-4MLB by North Korean proxy company GLOCOM, in brochure it was stated that it is controlled by laser beam guidance method, which was an upgrade designated Bulsae-3. Its use was first reported in 2014 in the ranks of the Izz ad-Din al-Qassam Brigades and the Al-Nasser Salah al-Deen Brigades.

title: anti-tank_missile

title: bgm-71_tow
body: The BGM-71 TOW ("Tube-launched, Optically tracked, Wire-guided", pronounced /Ààto ä/) is an [[United States Army|American]] crew-served, wire-guided [[anti-tank missile]]. First produced in 1970, TOW is one of the most widely used anti-tank guided missiles. It can be found in a wide variety of manually carried and vehicle-mounted forms, as well as widespread use on helicopters. Originally designed by Hughes Aircraft in the 1960s, the weapon is currently produced by RTX.

title: celeste_(animal_crossing)
body:
A red anthropomorphic [[owl]] from [[Animal Crossing]].

Celeste is [[Blathers (animal crossing)|]]' younger sister. Her character design is similar to his, except with the predominantly red color scheme, and a big pink bow on the back of her head. 

She's had different roles in various games of the series; working in an observatory, managing a gift shop, or appearing to inform the player about nightly meteor showers. In most games, her role is themed on outer space, stars and other celestial objects. (Hence her name.)

This makes Blathers and Celeste the "owl scientist siblings" of Animal Crossing: The older brother skilled in biology, and the younger sister skilled in astrophysics. 

h4. External links

* "Nookipedia: Celeste":https://nookipedia.com/wiki/Celeste

title: blathers_(animal_crossing)
body:
A brown anthropomorphic [[owl]] from [[Animal Crossing]].

He has appeared in most games of the series as the manager and curator of the village museum. His character design seems to take inspiration from a British college professor, from his green bowtie, to the pattern of his feathers, to some of the Britishisms he speaks with. 

While he's polite and friendly to a fault, it's a running gag of the series that he hates bugs. He'll accept bug donations for the museum, and he'll even educate the player on bug facts. But he does these things under dramatic duress. 

Has a red-colored sister named [[Celeste (animal crossing)|]].

title: japanese_white-eye
body:
A species of [[bird]].

The head and back of this small perching [[bird]] are olive-green, the throat may be bright yellow, and the belly is pale green or grey. It has a prominent pale white ring around each eye, for which it is named in both English and Japanese.

One of the native species of the Japanese islands, this bird has been depicted in Japanese art on numerous occasions, and historically was kept as a cage bird.

In 2018, molecular DNA evidence convinced scientists to combine this species with that of the warbling white-eye, by which name the Japanese white-eye is now officially known.

title: bleeding_heart_(flower)
body:
A common name for several genera of [[flower]]ing plants in the [[poppy (flower)|]] family ([i]Papaveraceae[/i]), native to East Asia.

The bleeding heart plants produce arching flower-bearing stems with hanging flowers. The flowers have a distinctive shape, resembling a conventional [[heart]], with narrow droplet-like petals beneath, hence the common name. Common flower colors are pink, purple-pink, red, and white. The leaves are lobed.

The personification of the Japanese aircraft carrier [i]Taihou[/i] in [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i]. Character design by [[Shimada Fumikane]], voiced by [[Noto Mamiko]].

She has [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[brown hair]], [[brown eyes]], and [[small breasts]]/[[flat chest]]. Her outfit consists of a [[white shirt|white]]/[[black shirt]] worn under a [[white shrug]], a collar piece patterned off her real-life bow with a [[kikumon]], [[grey corset]] armor, [[red skirt|red]]/dark [[green skirt|green]] [[pleated skirt]], black [[bike shorts]], [[black thighhighs]], [[black footwear|black]] [[rudder footwear]], and a metal [[hairband]]. Her [[rigging]] consists of her real-life hull and [[flight deck]] to her left (with magazine storage) and her real-life bridge to her right, with 10 cm twin [[anti-aircraft gun]] mounts on her waist. title: super_robot_wars_z3
body:
The third and final installment in the [[Super Robot Wars Z]] trilogy. Released on [[PlayStation 3]] and [[PlayStation Vita]], Z3 marks the first HD release in the SRW series. Like it's [[super robot wars z2|predecessor]], Z3 was released in two parts, the first (Jigoku-hen) in 2014 and the second (Tengoku-hen) in 2015. A third segment (Rengoku-hen) was available for a limited time through redemption codes included in first print copies of Tengoku-hen. This third segment is set between the two main games, and focuses primarily on the original aspects of the story.

Despite the graphical update, the Z3 games have faced criticism from fans due to many units and series being cut from the previous games, and a heavier focus on the original story elements as opposed to series roster's stories. Almost every series that debuted in the first game was notably absent in this entry.

title: serpent_(mobile_suit)
body:
[b]MMS-01 Serpent[/b]

A mass-produced heavy assault mobile suit from [[Gundam Wing: Endless Waltz|Endless Waltz]], utilized by the Maremaria army as they put Operation Meteor into action. The Serpent was a powerhouse of a mobile suit, depending on its armament outgunning anything less than one of the Gundams or the [[Tallgeese III]]. It was equipped with missile launchers in its shoulders and could be armed with a beam cannon, a double gatling gun derived from the [[Gundam Heavyarms Custom|Heavy Arms Custom]] and a powerful bazooka.

title: mother_superior_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Elder Nun, Grandma Nun.

The first of the Little Nuns, she arrived fifty years ago with a dream, a pair of [[duck|ducks]], and a [[Bernese mountain dog]] to oversee the building of the nunnery. Grandmotherly, caring, and respected by all.

* !post #6923270

title: father_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Priest, Padre, Brother Shades.

The only male human known to work at the nunnery, he is often seen to be put-upon and overworked. Despite his stern looks, he gets along with the nuns and seems to enjoy spending time with them (when not watching forlornly from the background). Never seen without his characteristic [[round eyewear|round]] [[sunglasses]].

body:

* !post #6906478

title: leaf_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Grey Bangs Nun.

Possibly the only nun in the nunnery clumsier than [[Clumsy Nun (diva)|]], she is often seen getting into various scrapes and accidents, and tends to sport at least one [[bandaid]] on her face. Enjoys [[gardening]].

* !post #6903158

body:

* !post #6899985

body:

title: freckles_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Strands Nun.

One of the older nuns with the least screentime, she frequently appears to [[sweatdrop]] at the others' antics. Something of a clean freak. She has [[black hair]] and [[freckles]].

* !post #6886071

title: star_nun_(diva)
body:
Star Nun is the leader of the older [[nun]]s. She is strict but fair, often doling out punishments to her misbehaving juniors in the form of red star stickers. She was mentored by [[Spicy Nun's mother (diva)|]] during her time at the nunnery, and in turn tends to be a regular minder of [[Spicy Nun (diva)|]] in the present. She has a [[star (symbol)|]] on her habit and commands an army of various birds, recognizable by their identical stars. Prodigious at [[fishing]]. Her [[wimple]] generally conceals all her hair. She has never been seen to open her eyes.

* !post #6882956

title: strict_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Grumpy Nun, Hairclips Nun, Scowly Nun.

While she tries to set a good example for the other nuns, she slips up often and is easily embarrassed. Mentor to [[Clumsy Nun (diva)|]] and long-term rival of [[Smug Nun (diva)|]], she has also developed something of a partnership with the nunnery's [[ostrich]]. She wears two [[hair flower|hair flowers]] and has a [[mole]] under her left eye.

* !post #6876578

title: sheep_nun_(diva)
body:
Sheep Nun is [[Froggy Nun (diva)|]]'s roommate and frequent minder. She bears the shenanigans of her fellow younger nuns with patience and good humor. As her name suggests, she loves sheep. She has [[freckles]] and rarely opens her eyes.

* !post #6865626

title: hungry_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Gluttonous Nun, Sly Nun.

Although her most obvious trait is her love of food and apparent bottomless pit of a stomach, she is also shown to be quite talented at sports. Often seen snacking in the background.

* !post #6855458

title: froggy_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Frog Nun, Curly Nun, Hook-Bang Nun.

An unusual girl with a perpetual [[:<]] face, Froggy Nun loves [[frog|frogs]] above all else, and is owner of a pet frog and several frog plushes. She also enjoys [[banana|bananas]], [[broccoli]], and anything green. Tries hard at all she does and is quick to tattle on others. Close friends with [[Sheep Nun (diva)|]], who acts as a big sister figure towards her. [[froggy nun's father (diva)|Her father]] is a local farmer.

* !post #6853049

title: spicy_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Chili Nun, Half-Bang Nun.

Spicy Nun is known for her skills in art (inherited from [[spicy nun's mother (diva)|her mother]]), her penchant for get-rich-quick schemes (which often backfire), and her love of [[chili pepper|chili peppers]]. Close friends with [[Clumsy Nun (diva)|]].

* !post #6841963

title: clumsy_nun_(diva)
body:
Also known as: Protagonist Nun, Main Nun.

She is the protagonist of the [[Little Nuns (diva)|]] series. As her name suggests, she is clumsy and often unlucky, but nevertheless irrepressibly cheerful. She was abandoned at the nunnery as a baby. Good friends (and often partners in crime) with [[Spicy Nun (diva)|]], and mentored by [[Strict Nun (diva)|]].

* !post #6838662

title: ogiue_chika
body:
[b]Ogiue Chika[/b] is a [[petite|short]], pretty, artistically talented and grumpy female [[otaku]]/[[fujoshi]] character from [[Genshiken]] who [[fujoshi|loves]] to read and draw [[yaoi]] manga.

She has big [[brown eyes]], [[black hair]] and a very peculiar hairstyle (in her earlier appearances) consisting of a paintbrush-like, tall [[topknot]].

Her physical features usually make her the target of the [[loli]] fantasies from most of the male members of the club. [spoilers]Ogiue officially ends up paired with [[Sasahara Kanji]] at the end of the first season of the Genshiken manga series.[/spoilers]

title: darth_vader
body:
The extremely popular and iconic anto-protagonist and main focus of the [[Star Wars]] films. David Prowse physically portrays Vader in the original trilogy, while [[James Earl Jones]] provides his voice in all of the films and some television series. 

[b]Darth Vader[/b] is a very powerful [[cyborg]] [[Sith]] Lord who wears black [[armor]] and [[cape]]. Once a heroic [[Jedi]] Knight, he turned his back on the Jedi Order, becoming the Right Hand of Emperor [[Palpatine]]. 

In addition to his formidable skill in [[lightsaber]] combat and his power in the Dark Side of the Force, Vader is also a very skilled and dangerous [[Galactic Empire (star Wars)|]] [[starfighter]] ace.

[spoiler]His name before his fall to the dark side of the Force was [[Anakin Skywalker]] and he is the father of both [[Luke Skywalker|Luke]] and [[princess leia|Leia]].

According to Star Wars creator [[George Lucas]], he is the "chosen one" who brought balance to the force by destroying the evil Emperor [[Palpatine]].[/spoiler]

title: northern_ireland
body:
The northeastern part of the island of [[Ireland]] governed by the [[United Kingdom]].

Historically, the region was separated from the rest of Ireland due to religious and political issues following Irish independence from the UK in 1922, with much of the area's Protestant-majority choosing to remain within the UK instead of joining the Catholic-majority "republican" Ireland. From the late 1960s up until the Good Friday Agreement in 1998, the area saw an era of protracted conflict known as "The Troubles", involving republican and loyalist paramilitary groups and the British government.

title: triforce
body:
The Triforce is the symbol of Hyrule in [[The Legend of Zelda]] series. The Triforce is split into three different parts, which in the games are always borne by the three central characters of the Zelda saga:

* The Triforce of Courage, which is held by [[Link]].
* The Triforce of Wisdom, which is held by [[Princess Zelda]].
* The Triforce of Power, which is held by [[Ganondorf]].

Whoever possesses all three parts of the Triforce can have any desire that he or she wants granted, but the effects of this wish upon the rest of Hyrule is largely based on whether the bearer of the Triforce is good or evil.

h4. See also

* [[mitsu uroko]] The symbol on which the Triforce was based.

title: brazilian_twitter_ban
body:
On August 31st, 2024, traffic to the social media site [[Twitter]] was blocked by telecom companies in Brazil under orders from the Brazilian supreme court.

The ban occurred as an escalation in a months long conflict between Twitter owner [[Elon Musk]] and Brazilian Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes after Twitter failed to designate a legal representative in Brazil. The feud between the two began in April, 2024 when Moraes issued a court order to Twitter to suspend certain accounts for allegedly spreading hate speech and misinformation. Musk later reversed the account suspensions and refused to comply with the court's orders, accusing them of censorship. After the ban occurred, Brazilian users announced their departure as a result of it, and many made their way to [[Bluesky]].

The ban ended on October 8th, after the social network complied with the court rulings, being released gradually.

The timing of the ban happened to coincide with the popular [[Worldwide Miku]] trend, leading to a number of fanart depicting [[Brazilian Miku]] and the effects of the ban.

title: serial_experiments_lain
body:
A [[cyberpunk]] [[horror (theme)|]] multimedia project including an anime series by Triangle Staff, a [[PlayStation 1]] game by Pioneer LCD, plus a number of soundtracks and artbooks.

By far the most widely known Lain product is the anime, released 1998. The game was released later the same year, although its scenario had been created first. [[Abe Yoshitoshi]] designed the characters for both, and mostly his art can be found in the art books, on the CD sleeves, etc. Various Lain products feature small amounts of [[4koma]] strips and manga pages by ABe, even one nine-page story that makes reference to both the anime and the game.

Due to Serial Experiments Lain's non-linear storytelling (even the anime is divided into "layers" instead of "episodes"), the plot is hard to summarize. Main themes include virtual world vs. reality, communication, loneliness, psychology, parapsychology, cyberculture and theology.

title: m._bison
body:
[b]M. Bison[/b], known as [b]Vega[/b] in Japan and neutrally referred to as [b]Dictator[/b] to avoid inter-region confusion, is one of the main villains and primary bosses of the [[Street Fighter]] games.

His first chronological appearance is in [[street fighter zero (series)|Street Fighter Zero 2]], as the head of an elusive criminal and military organization known as Shadaloo. Along with his aspirations for world conquest, M. Bison has been working on perfecting a lethal and deadly energy that will exponentially increase his fighting ability, an inherently evil energy he refers to as "Psycho Power".

Throughout the series, M. Bison occasionally attempts to increase his power by transferring his energy form into an artificially created physical body, thus increasing the limit of Psycho Power he can posses. His attempts were usually thwarted due to either the protagonist's actions destroying his physical body, or that the intended new body rebelled against him. His most famous duplicate body is [[Cammy White]].

[[Rose (Street Fighter)|]] is the other half of his soul, spiritually bound to him and wielding Psycho Power's opposite, Soul Power.

Though he has made numerous enemies, his most persistent and personal of foes include [[Chun-Li]] and [[Guile]], both seeking to avenge the death of her father and his friend [[Charlie Nash]], respectively.

After suffering a supposedly final death in [[Street Fighter V]], he mysteriously returned in [[Street Fighter 6]] in a weakened amnesiac form.

title: guinea_pig
body:
A domestic species of rodent originating from South America, related to the [[capybara]]. The guinea pig is tailless and herbivorous, with a stout, "potato-like" body shape and a size approximately twice that of a common rat. To the uninitiated, the guinea pig may resemble an oversized hamster.

Guinea pigs are highly vocal rodents and are noted for making a characteristic "wheek" sound when excited or hungry. This sound is rendered as "pui" in Japanese onomatopoeia. 

The scientific name of the species is [i]Cavia porcellus[/i]. It is sometimes also called "cavy" by breeders and owners. Guinea pigs were frequently used as experimental animals in research; hence the word "guinea pig" is often also used metaphorically to refer to experimental subjects.

title: jar-jar_binks
body:
Jar Jar Binks is a fictional character of the Gungan race from the [[Star Wars]] saga created by [[George Lucas]]. Jar Jar appears throughout the Star Wars prequel trilogy ‚Äì as a major character in [[star wars: The Phantom Menace|Episode I: The Phantom Menace]], with a smaller role in [[star wars: Attack of the Clones|Episode II: Attack of the Clones]], and with only a one-line cameo in  [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith|Episode III: Revenge of the Sith]].‚Äì as well as having a role in the television series [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]. The first fully computer-generated supporting character in a live-action film, he has been voiced by Ahmed Best in most of his appearances, who also acted out the character with prosthetics prior to the CGI work.

He was met with overwhelming dislike from both audiences and critics, and has been recognized as one of the most hated characters in Star Wars and the history of film in general, but the character's reception has changed as he has been championed by fans who had seen the prequels at the time of their release as children. He has also been defended by members of the prequels' production team.

title: equinox_(racehorse)
body:
[tn]Named after the time of the year when day and night are the same length. Alludes to the contrast between the names of his sire and dam (Black & White).[/tn]
Japanese [[horse|racehorse]]. Sired by [[Kitasan Black (racehorse)|]] and foaled by Chateau Blanche (by [[King Halo (racehorse)|]]).

A brown horse with a stocking on his right back leg and a wide blaze marking.

He gained fame, initially, for coming in second place for both the Satsuki-sho (to [[Geoglyph (racehorse)|]]) and the [[Tokyo Yushun]] (to [[Do Deuce (racehorse)|]]), before turning to the 2022 Autumn Tenno-sho, where he covered and overtook runner [[Panthalassa (racehorse)|]]'s 15 to 20 lengths lead, earning him his first GI title. Equinox then went on to win the 2022 [[Arima Kinen]] as well as the 2023 Dubai Sheema Classic in his overseas stint. Afterwards, he won the 2023 [[Takarazuka Kinen]] by a neck, almost losing to Through Seven Seas due to a fumble. He finished his streak by shattering the race record (and the world record on 2000m turf) at the 2023 Autumn Tenno-sho and dominating a very stacked 2023 Japan Cup. He was retired to stud afterwards, citing he would not have been ready in time for the Arima Kinen.

He is Kitasan Black's first G1-winning progeny and proved himself to be not only one of the best racehorses of his generation but also becoming the best rated racehorse in the world. His victory at the 2023 Japan Cup made him Japan's greatest earning racehorse and, had he continued, he would have been well on his way to become Japan's first 7 G1 winner on turf with [b]no[/b] classic race wins.

In the context of [[Umamusume]], as the son of [[Kitasan Black (umamusume)|]], most fan designs portray him in some form of [[japanese clothes|Japanese-style outfit]], often with a Sun & Moon motif with a red and blue color scheme that references the [[racing colors]] of Silk Racing, Equinox's owner. He is also depicted together with [[King Halo (umamusume)|]] and/or [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] on some occasions.

h4. See also

* [[Christophe Lemaire]] - Equinox's [[jockey]]

title: gunpod
body:
A [b]gunpod[/b] is a detachable pod or pack containing [[machine gun]]s or an automatic [[cannon]], mounted externally on a vehicle. They are usually used in [[military]] [[aircraft]].

Gunpods increase an air combat vehicle's firepower without occupying internal volume. When not required for a specific mission they can be omitted to save weight so the vehicle becomes lighter, faster and consumes less fuel.

Also used in some anime [[science fiction]] [[mecha]] series like [[MACROSS]].

The titular protagonist of [[Sousou no Frieren]].

She also wears [[black pantyhose]] and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]], and a pair of [[gold earrings|gold]] and red [[earrings]] on each ear. She also carries a [[mage staff]].

title: zalgo_commentary
body:
Zalgo is a form of text formatting associated with [[creepypasta]], [[demon|demons]], and [[eldritch abomination|eldritch abominations]].  It uses various tricks, particularly Unicode "combining diacritics":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combining_Diacritical_Marks and control characters that change the text flow direction. The result is text that appears corrupted, glitchy and partially overwritten by eldritch symbols.

Zalgo text originated in fan edits of the comic strip [[Garfield]], usually containing the phrase "He Comes!".

title: magma_taishi_(character)
body:
A character and protagonist from the [[Magma Taishi]] science fiction [[super robot]] manga and [[tokusatsu]] series from the 60s.

[b]Magma[/b] („Éû„Ç∞„Éû [i]Maguma[/i]) is a [[giant]] humanoid [[alien]] [[mecha]] hero forged in [[gold]] who just like his human-sized wife [[Mol (magma taishi)|]] and son [[Gam (magma taishi)|]], transforms into a giant [[rocket]]. He has long human-like [[blonde hair]] and also fires [[missile]]s out of a panel located in his chest, and shoots electrical bolts from his [[antennae]].

Magma is considered one of the earliest [[Transformers]], even before the anime super robot, [[Yuusha Raideen]], set the standard for the genre.

According to character creator [[Tezuka Osamu]], Magma is technically not a true [[super robot]], but an [[alien]] [[giant]] made of gold. However, because of his appearance and powers he has been classified as such since decades ago.

title: hopeless_masquerade
body:
A [[Touhou]] fighting game, officially designated as "Touhou 13.5" (as its events take place between [i][[Ten Desires]][/i] and [i][[Double Dealing Character]][/i]).  A demo with three playable characters was released 30 December 2012 at [[Comiket]] 83; the full version followed 26 May 2013 during [[Reitaisai]] 10 (alongside the demo for [i]Double Dealing Character[/i]).

The storyline centers on representatives of the three major faiths in [[Gensokyo]] -- Shinto, Buddhism, and Taoism -- battling it out in the wake of an overall crisis of faith in the Human Village.

In addition, a wide variety of other characters from the franchise make cameo appearances in the backgrounds of each stage.  Among others appearing in this fashion are, for the first time in any official Touhou game, [[Morichika Rinnosuke]] and [[Motoori Kosuzu]].

title: finding_nemo
body:
Finding Nemo is a 2003 American animated comedy-drama adventure film produced by [[pixar|Pixar Animation Studios]] for Walt Disney Pictures.
It tells the story of an overprotective clownfish named Marlin who, along with a forgetful regal blue tang named Dory, searches for his missing son Nemo. Along the way, Marlin learns to take risks and comes to terms with Nemo taking care of himself.

title: mr._satan
body:
A character from [[Dragon Ball Z]]. Also known as [b]Hercule Satan[/b] in the Funimation dub, he's the World Martial Arts Champion and the (self-proclaimed) protector of Earth. Father of [[Videl]]. His real name is [b]Mark[/b]. 

Initially introduced as a boastful, loud-mouthed comic relief. Although Satan is very strong for a human, he is no match for the various super fighters within the series, with him ending up running away from any threats and being viewed as a coward by those around him. He does, however, posses a strong sense of justice and luck, as Satan occasionally using his worldwide fame among ordinary earthlings to aid the protagonists in the fight. <spoilers>Most notably convincing the earthlings to spare their spirit energy to create the [[genki dama]] during [[Son Goku]]'s final fight against [[Kid Buu]] by using his name.</spoilers>

Voiced by [[Gouri Daisuke]] (1993-2010) and [[Ishizuka Unshou]] (2010-2018). Voiced by [[Ricardo Brust]] in the latin american dub.

title: bitter_glasse_(umamusume)
body:
[[Umamusume]] game-only character. Member of Team First under Acting Chairwoman [[Kashimoto Riko]].

[[Horse girl]]. Has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair|brown]] hair and [[brown eyes]]. She has [[dark skin]] and she also wears an ornament and ribbon around [b]her right ear[/b].

Like [[Happy Meek (umamusume)|]], Bitter Glasse is an "original umagirl", i.e. not based on any particular real-life horse. However, as it is often the case with popular pop culture, there's a real-life horse named [i]after[/i] her.

Bitter Glace (note the different spelling) is a bay [b]filly[/b] (not a colt as one would expect from the ear decoration placement) sired by Rulership and foaled by Anthology. Rulership is a son of [[King Kamehameha (umamusume)|]] and [[Air Groove (umamusume)|]] while Anthology is a daughter of [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] and Pops (herself a daughter of [[Sunday Silence (racehorse)|]]).

As an apparent nod to her, Bitter Glasse is said to go to the Miho dormitory according to dorm head [[Hishi Amazon (umamusume)|]].

h5. External links

* "Umamusume Official Character Bio: Bitter Glasse":[https://umamusume.jp/character/bitterglasse]

title: happy_meek_(umamusume)
body:
Character from [i][[Umamusume]][/i].

[[Kiryuuin Aoi]]'s charge. Happy Meek isn't based on any particular racehorse but she seems to be the only genuine white horse of the franchise (dominant white is an extremely uncommon color for throughbreds - very few thrived in the racetrack and only one horse ([[Sodashi (racehorse)|]]) has ever won a G1 race - all the other white-haired horse girls were actually based on gray horses). That being said, she is likely modeled either on Hakutaiyu, Japan's first white horse or on Shirayukihime's several descendants (like Sodashi herself).

Happy Meek is a [[horse girl]] with [[short_hair|short]] [[white hair]] (usually portrayed as an off-white), [[pink eyes]] with a flower hairclip over her left temple and an ornament made out of small flowers around [b]her right ear[/b] (although, in her case, this might be irrelevant).

h5. External links

* "Umamusume Official Character Bio: Happy Meek":[https://umamusume.jp/character/happymeek]

title: little_cocon_(umamusume)
body:
[[Umamusume]] game-only character. Member of Team First under Acting Chairwoman [[Kashimoto Riko]].

[[Horse girl]]. Has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair|blonde]] hair (with a single [[blue hair|blue]] [[streaked hair|highlight]]) and [[green eyes]]. She also wears a [[purple bow|purple]] [[hair bow]] positioned in front and to the right of [b]her right ear[/b].

This chestnut colt is a son of Big Arthur and foaled by Break Dancer. He is a sire-line grandson of [[Sakura Bakushin O (umamusume)|]] and, on the mother's side, a descendant of [[Sunday Silence (racehorse)|]] through Dance in the Dark.

title: fanny_pack
body: A fanny pack (known as a bum bag in the UK) is a small fabric pouch usually secured with a zipper and worn by use of a strap usually around the hips or waist. One style trend involves wearing the pack across the chest. The word 'fanny' is American slang for a person's [[ass|buttocks]]. The word 'bum' means the same thing in Britain and many Commonwealth countries.

title: komeiji_satori
body:
The "Girl Feared by Evil Spirits". Stage 4 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Subterranean Animism]] and the title character in [[Foul Detective Satori]].

Mistress of the Palace of Earth Spirits whose power as a "satori":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satori_%28folklore%29 - to read minds with her "[[third eye]]" appendage - caused even youkai to fear her, but made her well-loved by animals. She is the master of [[Kaenbyou Rin]] and [[Reiuji Utsuho]], keepers of the Hell of Blazing Fires, and older sister of [[komeiji_koishi|Koishi]].
